Backend /dashboard/tester/:userId/test-runs:
- Now returns ALL scenarios for any run the tester participates in,
  not just their own assigned scenarios. Each row is tagged with
  is_mine=true/false so the frontend can distinguish.
- Without this, a tester assigned to 1 of 2 scenarios would only see
  1 scenario, making the run card show '1/1' instead of '1/2'.

Frontend TesterDashboardPage:
- My Scenarios KPI: now counts only is_mine rows (assigned to this tester)
- Run card To Do/In Progress/Done stats: now reflect all scenarios in the
  run so the breakdown matches the total shown in 'X/Y scenarios'
- Pass Rate: changed from '% of runs completed' to '% of terminal
  executions that passed' — a meaningful metric when many test cases fail.
  Old formula (completedRuns/totalRuns) gave 0% or 100% per run which
  was not useful. New formula counts passed vs total executed test cases.
- Pass Rate hint updated to 'Steps passed vs total executed'
---
 artifacts/api-server/src/routes/executions.ts | 30 +++++++++++++++----
 .../src/pages/TesterDashboardPage.tsx         | 17 ++++++-----
 2 files changed, 35 insertions(+), 12 deletions(-)

diff --git a/artifacts/api-server/src/routes/executions.ts b/artifacts/api-server/src/routes/executions.ts
index 5349091..ec6f88f 100644
--- a/artifacts/api-server/src/routes/executions.ts
+++ b/artifacts/api-server/src/routes/executions.ts
@@ -131,16 +131,30 @@ router.get("/dashboard/tester/:userId/test-runs", async (req, res, next) => {
   try {
     const userId = Number(req.params.userId);
 
-    const assignedUseCases = await db.query.testRunUseCases.findMany({
+    // Find all test runs where this user is assigned to at least one scenario
+    const myAssignments = await db.query.testRunUseCases.findMany({
       where: eq(schema.testRunUseCases.assigned_tester_id, userId),
+      with: { testRun: true },
+    });
+
+    if (myAssignments.length === 0) {
+      res.json([]);
+      return;
+    }
+
+    // Get unique run IDs this tester participates in
+    const myRunIds = [...new Set(myAssignments.map((a) => a.test_run_id))];
+
+    // Fetch ALL scenarios for those runs (not just the tester's own scenarios)
+    // so the run card can show accurate overall progress
+    const allUseCases = await db.query.testRunUseCases.findMany({
+      where: sql`${schema.testRunUseCases.test_run_id} IN (${sql.join(myRunIds.map(id => sql`${id}`), sql`,`)})`,
       with: {
         testRun: {
           with: {
             project: true,
             executions: {
-              with: {
-                stepResults: true,
-              },
+              with: { stepResults: true },
             },
           },
         },
@@ -148,7 +162,13 @@ router.get("/dashboard/tester/:userId/test-runs", async (req, res, next) => {
       },
     });
 
-    res.json(assignedUseCases);
+    // Tag each row so the frontend knows which scenarios belong to this tester
+    const result = allUseCases.map((uc) => ({
+      ...uc,
+      is_mine: uc.assigned_tester_id === userId,
+    }));
+
+    res.json(result);
   } catch (err) {
     next(err);
   }
